step.tex:
\begin{align}

\dfrac{\sin^3 x +\cos^3 x}{\sin^2 x \cos^2 x}
&= \dfrac{\sin^3 x}{\sin^2 x \cos^2 x } + \dfrac{\cos^3 x}{\sin^2 x \cos^2 x} \\
&= \dfrac{\sin x}{\cos^2 x} + \dfrac{\cos x}{\sin^2 x} \\
&= \tan x \sec x + \cot x \, \mathrm{cosec} \, x \\
\end{align}

step.reason:
\int \tan x \sec x \, dx = \sec x + C_1 \\
\int \cot x \, \mathrm{cosec} \, x ) \, dx = - \mathrm{cosec}\, x + C_2 \\
\text{where } C_1 \text{ and } C_2  \text{ are constants of integration.}
